DICATED AND UNCONVENTIONAL LIBRARY WORKS' IMPRESSIONS FROM BIRMINGHAM.BIRMINGHAM HAS 1 OF THE LARGEST AND BEST LIBRARY SYSTEMS IN EUROPE, WITH ATOTAL LIBRARY BUDGET OF OVER 7 MILLION POUNDS AND OVER 2 MILLION STOCK ITEMSFOR 1 MILLION INHABITANTS. STRIKING FEATURES OF THE CENTRAL LIBRARY INCLUDE AQUICK REFERENCE AND TRADE SECTION OF OVER 7,000 WORKS AND 7 REFERENCEDEPARTMENTS. THE 45 BRANCHES DIVIDE INTO 4 REGIONAL GROUPS IN ORDER TOMAINTAIN CLOSE CONTACT WITH THE CENTRAL LIBRARY BUT YET RETAIN A MEASURE OFINDEPENDENCE. MANY COPE WITH SOCIAL PROBLEMS, ESPECIALLY IN THE INNER CITYAREA. AN ETHNIC MINORITIES LIBRARIAN COORDINATES ALL SERVICES TO FOREIGNREADERS. STUDY GROUPS ORGANISE PROJECTS ON REFERENCE MATERIAL, LIBRARYPUBLICATIONS, RADIO PROGRAMMES AND STAFF TRAINING. IN CONTRAST WITH MANYGERMAN LIBRARIES, SERVICES FOR CHILDREN ARE GIVEN PARTICULAR PROMINENCE; INADDITION TO SECTIONS IN EACH BRANCH LIBRARY THERE ARE ALSO 2 CENTRALCHILDREN'S LIBRARIES